title: Stunning gardens
text:
The Queen Victoria Gardens are Melbourne's memorial to Queen Victoria. Located opposite the Victorian Arts Centre and National Gallery of Victoria, bounded by St Kilda Road, Alexandra Avenue, and Linlithgow Avenue.

Queen Victoria's reign started in 1837, two years after the initial European settlement of Melbourne, and upon her death in 1901 it was thought appropriate to declare an enduring monument to her reign.

title: Great service
text: This bus was very convenient and comfortable to get to the airport and back to Melbourne. Very easy to use. SkyBus operates six services from Melbourne Tullamarine Airport providing fast airport transfers to Melbourne City, Southbank and Docklands, St Kilda and Frankston and bayside suburbs and Melbourne's western and east suburbs.

title: The best tour
text: A majority of the tours to the Twelve Apostles are full-day tours leaving from Melbourne in the early morning. There are many stops and photo opportunities along the way as you drive down the Great Ocean Road, such as Loch Ard Gorge, Apollo Bay, and Port Campbell. Discover the native wildlife. We have seen koalas, a mother and a little one, which was great experience.

title: Lovely street art
text: Hosier Lane is located between Swanston and Russell streets, extending from Flinders Street through to Flinders Lane. Hosier Lane today is a brightly lit lane well known for its quirky bars and the stencil graffiti art which adorns the lane's brick walls.

title: Vibrant little lane
text: Lane full of coffee shops and restaurants. It is a short, narrow laneway in the Central Business District that runs north-south from Flinders Street to Flinders Lane and is situated in-between Swanston Street and Elizabeth Street. Degraves, as the street is colloquially known, is famous for its alfresco dining options. It is a perfect example of Melbourne's famous coffee culture and street art scene. For these reasons it has become a popular tourist destination.

title: Historic landmark
text: Arcade with shops and beautiful design similar as Galleria Vittoria Emanuelle in Milan, but in that one in Milan there are more of luxury shops. Still worth seeing it.

title: Memorial
text: The Shrine of Remembrance is a war memorial in Melbourne, Victoria, Australia, located in Kings Domain on St Kilda Road. It was built to honour the men and women of Victoria who served in World War I, but is now a memorial to all Australians who have served in war. Impressive landmark and nice view to the city skyline.

title: Free tram
text: It’s a free tram only around city circle. Quite useful to get to the attractions and to the streets, if you don’t want to walk a lot.

title: Amazing Trip
text: We had transfer to the port. We had a lovely weather so we could relax in the sun. Great cruise to three Greek Islands Hydra, Poros and Aegina. We admired the most beautiful Hydra island. Nice shops, windmill and restaurants. We just had limited time to spend on each island. The entertainment on the boat was great and we enjoyed Greek songs and Greek dancing. It was great day for us.
place: Hydra, Poros and Egina Day Cruise from Athens with Optional VIP Upgrade

title: Ancient temple
text: An ancient Greek temple on the north side of the Acropolis of Athens in Greece which was dedicated to both Athena and Poseidon.

title: The Academy
text: Academy founded by Plato, Socrates studied there for twenty years. There is statue of Socrates, Plato and other Greek Gods.

title: Cathedral of Athens
text: Another magnificent historical landmark of Athens, you must see. The Metropolitan Cathedral of Athens is one of the grandest churches in this ancient city. In Greek Orthodox style, it is lavishly decorated inside.

title: Old Athens
text: Lovely historical neighbourhood of Athens. Plaka was developed mostly around the ruins of Ancient Agora of Athens, situated between Syntagma and Monastiraki square. The largest and most central street in Plaka is Adrianou Street.

title: Syntagma square
text: Syntagma Square is the central square of Athens. The square is named after the Constitution that Otto, the first King of Greece, was obliged to grant after a popular and military uprising on 3 September 1843. It is located in front of the 19th century Old Royal Palace, housing the Greek Parliament since 1934. We have been watching the change of guards there.

title: The Acropolis of Athens
text: Lovely ancient history, majestic Acropolis citadel. Nice walk to the top, great view to the city underneath. The most popular tourist attraction in Athens. It does worth it. We really enjoyed it as well as lovely weather.

title: Sirikul Mansion
text: Nice relaxing place and close to the airport. Comfortable and clean rooms. Good for the price. Helpful staff, they arranged trasnport for us from hotel to the boat to Koh Yao Noi island. We felt great and relaxed there.

title: Pasai beach
text: One of Koh Yao Noi’s main beaches, Pasai Beach is a quiet strip of sand about 2 kilometres long, with the near-deserted tarmac road running directly parallel with it. Beautiful nature for relaxing with drinks and sunshine....

title: The head of a sandstone Budha statue
text: The head of a sandstone Buddha statue nestled in the tree roots beside the minor chapels of Wat Maha That, Phra Nakhon Si Ayutthaya Province, Thailand. The temple is one of the most tourist and photographic attractions in the UNESCO World Heritage Site of Ayutthaya, an ancient capital of Siam.

title: Ancient city
text: Great tour to Ayuthaya from Bangkok. Great history and guide throughout this ancient city. It does worth it to get to know the history of Thailand. Ayuthaya used to be the capital city before Bangkok. We also enjoyed feeding lovely elephats with the "tones" of bananas And with those magnificent temples I felt like I am in Angkor Wat.

title: Views from the river
text: We took this boat to get to Wat Arun. Express transport between stops in Bangkok city. Nice view from the boat and you can see the sights from the river....

title: Magnificent temple of dawn
text: Wat Arun, locally known as Wat Chaeng, is situated on the west bank of the Chao Phraya River. It is easily one of the most stunning temples in Bangkok, because the design is very different to the other temples you can visit in Bangkok. Wat Arun is partly made up of colourfully decorated spires and stands majestically over the water. We took lovely pics with nice views. We got there by ferry.

title: Famous road
text: Famous road for tourists. We stayed at the hotel located there.... There are various restaurants and bars, or massage if you’re up for it, stalls with souvenirs and clothes. And what a night life on Khalsa road... You need to try it.

title: The Palace
text: Nice historical place.... Magnificent complex of buildings located in the old city of Bangkok. The mos famous landmark is a must see. Just don’t forget about dress code. This means no short pants, no shirts without sleeves, no bare feet.

title: Nice airport with a great brands
text: We were heading back home and we had to spend some money so we did some shopping for the cosmetics and some more souvenirs. We enjoyed lovely food and drinks.

title: Nice and close to the airport
text: Nice hotel and clean rooms and very comfortable. Helpful staff and only ten minutes walk from the airport. Transfer available from the hotel as well. Good for money. We used transport to Bang Rong Pier to go to little island Koh Yao Noi.

title: Ann Frank
text:
Interesting story about 15 years old clever girl and writer... In her diaries she described the feelings of people forced to live in hiding and if they wanted to get fresh air they had to go through the attic on the roof. Very sad that they found them just a few month before the end of the World War II...
This attraction is very popular and people can get tickets online till 15.30 and then people who prefer to pay cash can go in from 15.30 till closed. We got there about 16.30 and we have been waiting for one hour to get in.

title: Lovely windmills you must see
text: Zaanse Schans is a neighbourhood of Zaandam, near Zaandijk, Netherlands. It has a collection of well-preserved historic windmills and houses... Lovely village and you can look inside any windmill you like... We took metro and then train, it was about one hour to get there.

title: Lovely spare ribs
text: We had a lovely dinner there with a free drink for a reasonable price... Staff and service was great. The restaurant is in town centre, very convenient. We liked it.

title: Caminito, La Boca
text:
We went there to see lovely colourful houses in Caminito - little walkway in Spanish. this is a street museum, area for artists selling their work. We also enjoyed famous tango in the street and made a lovely pictures with the dancers.
La Boca is a working-class area with brightly painted zinc shacks that evoke the district’s early immigrant days. We visited La Bombonera stadium which is the home ground of Boca Juniors soccer team.
It was a bit rainy when we got there but sun came out in a while. And we enjoyed these colourful area.
But also I must say that before we went there we were told at our hotel that this is rough area and not to were gold to attract the attantion of the burglars. We did not have any problems as we went during the day. I think it is more risky in the evening.

title: Beach in Barcelona
text: It was lovely sunny day when we were there. It was a nice beach with a long promenade. We made a few pics and enjoyed this place.

title: Magnific monument
text: We have seen Arc de Triomphe in Paris and this one in Barcelona is breathtaking as well. Really nice place to go and worth to see it.

title: Magnificent monument
text: Another magnificent monument in Barcelona and great work of Gaudi... The attraction you can not see anywhere else. I am grateful I could see this great art.

title: A must see
text: My husband is a big fun of football and we go to football stadium in every city. W enjoyed this experience and it was a nice stadium and interesting history about the football club.

title: Must see attraction
text: My husband is a big fun of football and we visit football stadiums in every city. This one was lovely and we enjoyed its history.

title: Great place and view
text: We love history so we really enjoyed this place. There also is a magnificent view to the city and we got there by funicular. It connects Montjuic with the Metro Transportation system at Paral·lel Station, Lines 2 and 3. It’s the fastest an easiest way to get to Montjuic when you’re in the Metro. The trip is already included on your regular Metro ticket. It is a lovey place and we had a fun on the way there.

title: The longest street in Barcelona
text: We walked through this street full of shops, restaurants, bars and attractions too. We have see some artists there as well. It is crowded so watch the burglars.

title: Beautiful Placa Espanya
text: Lovely Placa Espanya, lovely area, lovely view with magic fountain and Museu Nacional d'Art de Catalunya. It does worth it for a great view.

title: Historical San Telmo
text: Along the streets of the historical San Telmo Neighborhood there is the history of the best of Argentine graphic humor. Walking through this area we loved and admired San Telmo animations. There is a museum of humour nearby. This is one of the city's oldest neighbourhoods, with cobbled streets and bohemian charm.

title: Unusual Flower
text: Floralis Genérica is a sculpture made of steel and aluminum located in Plaza de las Naciones Unidas, Avenida Figueroa Alcorta, Buenos Aires, nowhere else to see...20m-high, 18-tonne sculpture dominates the Plaza de las Naciones Unidas. It is controlled by sun.The six steel petals open at 8am each morning, and close at sunset, when the centre of the sculpture emanates a red glow. The petals also close in high winds in order to protect the sculpture.

title: Women's bridge
text: Landmark rotating footbridge designed by Santiago Calatrava. The bridge represents a couple dancing tango, with the white mast symbolising the man and the curve of the bridge, the woman. It has a large turning mechanism, allowing it to swing open to allow sailing ships to pass. The bridge was constructed in Spain and donated to Buenos Aires through a private donation. Pictoresque landmark for me.

title: Japanese Garden
text: One of the largest Japanese gardens of its type in the world outside Japan. Nice for walk and it's quiet relaxing area.

title: Famous street
text: It has many big brand stores, as well as souvenir shops. It's good to grab something to eat there and it's great entertainment because of talented tango dancers in this Florida Street. I really enjoyed my time there and I felt very well entertained with tango.

title: Cafe Tortoni
text: We are chasing up for history again... The city's oldest and best preserved historic cafe established in 1858. Nice to see it.

title: Porto Pirata
text: We went there for a drink, we liked the decoration... it gives us a feeling like we would be on a pirate's ship... Nice waiters and reasonable price for a pint of beer.

title: La Plata
text: Cathedral is famous for its ceremonial wedding of Eva Peron. It was nice cathedral and nice escape from Buenos Aires by bus.

title: Long and wide street
text: You can find lots of restaurants there, shops and of course Obelisc with BA letters where people make pictures of it. Really impressive. Good for a long walk.

title: Famous cemetery
text: We were interested in to see Eva Peron's grave. We had a walk through this cemetery and had a look inside those fascinating mausoleums. It was interesting to see indeed.

title: Pigeons plaza
text: Lots of pigeons around this place....We took interesting pictures with them. This is very crowded place and shops as well.

title: Very impressive building
text: Another impressive artwork from Gaudi with the great fantasy... Building like from the fairytale... it's a must see attraction in Barcelona. Thumbs up.

title: Nice dinner
text: Lovely food, place, and friendly staff. It was really delicious food. Will come again as it does worth it to go there....

title: Ferry to Brixham
text: It's nice to go in summer to enjoy the ferry, well worth the money. It was a nice trip and we'll do it again.

title: Nice pub
text: I've been here many times for a few drinks. It is a great place for a lovely dinner or Christmas party.

title: Nice bistro
text: I've been here several times. After swimming we pooped in for nice cup of coffee. They serve a nice food there....

title: Beautifully Park
text: I felt like Alice in Wonderland when I was there. The most beautiful park and art of talented Gaudi, which I have ever seen. It worth to go there....

title: Gastown
text: Nice place to walk and we enjoyed making pictures around the clock. It has got its history.... There are lots of brewery pubs and souvenir shops.

title: Lovely cathedral
text: We were a bit disappointed as when we got there it was closed and we could not get in. But we admired this cathedral from outside...
place: Cathedral of Our Lady of the Holy Rosary

title: Granville island market
text: You can get there by False creak ferries and aquabus. There was a wide range of food.... and bear tasting.

title: History museum
text: We are a big funs of the cities history.... So this museum will take you back to history and how people lived in the past... It makes us feel grateful what we've got now...

title: Library
text: When we saw this building we would not think of library at all. It has got interesting appearance. We could not resist not to take a picture...

title: Lovely place
text: Nice place to be when it is a sunny day and to have a rest and picnic after long walk around the city.
